ClusterAclsMissingRemediation = Add a computer entry for the cluster to the AD OU '{0}', and grant the CreateChild and ReadProperty ACEs, or run deployment script.
SecurityGroupsMissingRemediation = Could not find the following security groups in the Users OU: '{0}'.  Add them, or run deployment script.
HostSecurityGroupsMissingRemediation = The computer '{0}' is not part of the following security groups: '{1}'.  Add them, or run deployment script.
GmsaAccountsMissingRemediation = These gMSA accounts are not properly configured: '{0}'.  Add them, or run deployment script.
NestedSecurityGroupsMissingRemediation = The security group '{0}' is missing the following memberships: '{1}'.  Add the required nested security group memberships, or run deployment script.
OuInheritanceBlockedMissingRemediation = Set the GpoInheritanceBlocked property of the AD OUs to true, or run deployment script.
NcDnsWorkaroundMissingRemediation = Add a DNS "A" record for 'nc' in the '{0}' zone, or run deployment script.
NotRunningElevated = ActiveDirectory module is not present and this script is not running elevated.  Unable to install RSAT tools to execute test.
RsatCapabilityPresentButCantImport = Found installed Windows capability '{0}', but ActiveDirectory module could not be imported.
RsatOptionalFeaturePresentButCantImport = Found enabled Windows optional feature '{0}', but ActiveDirectory module could not be imported.
MissingModuleAndRsat = Unable to find ActiveDirectory module.  This is likely because you are running on a client OS without first installing the RSAT package.  Please ensure RSAT is installed before running this command.
FailedToInstallRsat = Attempt to install missing ActiveDirectory module failed.  Inner exception: {0}
ModuleStillMissingAfterRsatInstall = RSAT tools are installed, but ActiveDirectory module cannot be found.  A restart may be required.
FailToLoadModuleAfterRsatInstall = Cannot find ActiveDirectory module, even after taking steps to install it.  Inner exception: {0}
KdsRootKeyMissingRemediation = Add a root key to the Key Distribution Service
CurrentUserFailureSummary = The ActiveDirectory user account '{0}' is ineligible to be used as a deployment user: {1}
CurrentUserMissingSGMembership = the user is missing membership to the following security group(s): ({0})
CurrentUserMissingCreateAndDeleteComputerObjectPermission = the user is missing the create and delete computer object permission to the organizational unit '{0}'
CurrentUserMissingReadObjectPermissions = the user is missing the read object permission to the organizational unit '{0}'
CurrentUserMissingMsfveRecoverInformationobjectsPermissions = the user is missing the msFVE-RecoverInformationobjects permission to the organizational unit '{0}'
CurrentUserHasExcessSGMemberships = the user is a member of extraneous security group(s): ({0})
ADUserNotFound = Unable to find user '{0}' in AD under OU '{1}'
